i:44;s:53:"Here are some other telltale signs of track problems.";i:45;s:88:"Gaps between the rollers and the rail components that are misshapen and a rubbing noise.";i:46;s:47:"How to Fix a Garage Door That Wont Lock Step 1.";i:47;s:56:"Locate the square hole on the inside of each door track.";i:48;s:54:"The hole will be around the height of the second door.";i:49;s:67:"Close the garage door and attempt to lock the door from the inside.";i:50;s:42:"Locate where the ends of the locking bars.";i:51;s:119:"If your garage door is stuck due to this reason simply make sure its path is clear and the bottom of the door is clean.";i:52;s:23:"Limit settings are off.";i:53;s:106:"If you notice that your garage door is not staying closed and is instead immediately springing open again.";i:54;s:104:"As garage doors lead directly into our homes it can be a stressful situation when your garage wont shut.";i:55;s:206:"We hope you have a better understanding of what may be happening when your door is stuck and how you can get to the root of the issue without spending on unnecessary maintenance or making the problem worse.";i:56;s:137:"The spring has either become dry dirty and needs some lubrication or the spring needs an extra turn or two to increase the lifting power.";i:57;s:168:"First of all oil the door as per the instructions in your handbook and open and close the door a few times to let the oil penetrate then check the opening action again.";i:58;s:115:"Starting about a week ago the latch on my back door knob wont retract into the doorknob unless I turn the doorknob.";i:59;s:109:"This means to close my door properly I have to unlock the doorknob turn it close the door then lock it again.";i:60;s:87:"If I try to just close it the latch wont retract and just bangs against the door frame.";i:61;s:23:"Unlock the garage door.";i:62;s:101:"Lower down from the emergency release kit another lock next to a handle keeps the door itself closed.";i:63;s:73:"With your key unlock the door and turn the handle so that it is vertical.";i:64;s:119:"Pull the garage door straight up with your hands and make sure it stays open before driving your car inside the garage.";i:65;s:107:"Before beginning ensure that the garage opener is not plugged in and power has been cut to the garage door.";i:66;s:28:"Remove indoor control panel.";i:67;s:122:"Locate the garage door control panel and remove it from the wall then using a screwdriver disconnect the control panel by.";i:68;s:106:"When a garage door wont function properly the source of the problem could be in any number of given areas.";i:69;s:208:"Whether you have a garage door that wont open all the way or a garage door that wont open manually it is best to know the most common causes of each problem and whether it is necessary to call a professional.";}}